Before adding tests, there is a logic issue in the current service: these flags are initialized but never updated:

```java
boolean anySalesPointChanged = false;
boolean anyRelationshipCreated = false;
boolean anyRelationshipChanged = false;
```

Also, the result of `updateRelationship(...)` is currently ignored. That means the `RECORD_UPDATED` branch and part of the `RECORD_CREATED` branch may never execute.

## 1. Fix the relationship flags first

Replace the relationship section with:

```java
Optional<PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity> existingRelationship =
        relationshipRepository
                .findByPersonUserIdAndSalesPointIdAndRelationshipType(
                        user.getUserId(),
                        salesPoint.getSalesPointId(),
                        relationshipType
                );

boolean relationshipCreated = existingRelationship.isEmpty();

PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity relationship =
        existingRelationship.orElseGet(
                PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity::new
        );

boolean relationshipChanged = updateRelationship(
        relationship,
        user,
        salesPoint,
        relationshipType,
        workingRelationship
);

relationshipRepository.save(relationship);

anyRelationshipCreated |= relationshipCreated;
anyRelationshipChanged |= relationshipChanged;
```

This is important:

```java
anyRelationshipCreated |= relationshipCreated;
anyRelationshipChanged |= relationshipChanged;
```

Without those two lines, your response calculation is incorrect.

For the sales point, at minimum track whether it was created:

```java
Optional<SalesPointEntity> existingSalesPoint =
        salesPointRepository.findBySalesPointId(
                pointOfSalesRequest.getId()
        );

boolean salesPointCreated = existingSalesPoint.isEmpty();

SalesPointEntity salesPoint =
        existingSalesPoint.orElseGet(SalesPointEntity::new);

// Populate or update the sales-point fields here.
salesPoint.setSalesPointId(pointOfSalesRequest.getId());

salesPoint = salesPointRepository.save(salesPoint);

anySalesPointChanged |= salesPointCreated;
```

If the sales-point request contains other mutable fields, use an `updateSalesPoint(...)` method that returns whether anything changed.

