## Potential Mockito issue with nested DTO calls

The test above uses calls such as:

```java
request.getMetadata().getCorrelationId()
```

Your `request` mock will return `null` unless the nested objects are separately mocked.

The simplest fix is to declare the request with deep stubs:

```java
@Mock(answer = Answers.RETURNS_DEEP_STUBS)
private As400UserSnapshotRequest request;
```

Required import:

```java
import org.mockito.Answers;
```

Then this works:

```java
when(request.getMetadata().getCorrelationId())
        .thenReturn("correlation-123");
```

Alternatively, create separate mocks for metadata, source and person. Separate mocks are cleaner, but deep stubs keep this first test class shorter.

