# 4. Use a constant for the maximum error length

Replace:

```java
int maximumLength = 2000;
```

with a class constant:

```java
private static final int MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH = 2000;
```

Then:

```java
private String limitErrorMessage(String message) {
    if (message == null) {
        return null;
    }

    return message.length() <= MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH
            ? message
            : message.substring(
                    0,
                    MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH
            );
}
```

You can cover all three branches through Ping failure tests:

```java
@Test
void shouldLimitLongPingErrorMessage() {
    service = createService(true);

    String longMessage = "x".repeat(2500);

    when(userRepository.findByGpsGroupNumber("testuser"))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    when(salesPointRepository.findBySalesPointId("POS-001"))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    when(relationshipRepository
            .findByPersonUserIdAndSalesPointIdAndRelationshipType(
                    anyString(),
                    anyString(),
                    anyString()
            ))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    org.mockito.Mockito.doThrow(
            new RuntimeException(longMessage)
    ).when(pingUserClient)
            .createUser(any(UserEntity.class));

    assertThrows(
            RuntimeException.class,
            () -> service.synchronize(request)
    );

    org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor<UserEntity> captor =
            org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor.forClass(UserEntity.class);

    verify(userRepository, org.mockito.Mockito.atLeast(2))
            .save(captor.capture());

    UserEntity savedUser =
            captor.getAllValues()
                    .get(captor.getAllValues().size() - 1);

    assertEquals("FAILED", savedUser.getPingSyncStatus());
    assertNotNull(savedUser.getPingLastError());
    assertEquals(
            2000,
            savedUser.getPingLastError().length()
    );
}
```

The key production fix is the aggregation of the relationship flags. Without that fix, tests for `RECORD_UPDATED` will correctly fail because that response branch is currently unreachable.
